From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000034 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Sun, 6 Jul 2026 15:05:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: steelhead: don't select HAVE_HW_BREAKPOINT (HS debug locked)

The Nexus Q's OMAP4460 is a fused HS part with secure debug locked, so
enable_monitor_mode() can never set DSCR.MDBGEN -- it logged
"hw-breakpoint: Failed to enable monitor mode on CPU 0" every boot and
perf/ptrace hardware watchpoints cannot function regardless. Stock 3.0.8
did not build the feature (no hw_breakpoint symbols in its image). Drop
the arch select so the feature is not built: matches stock, removes the
boot warning, zero functional loss on this silicon. This kernel builds
only for steelhead, so dropping it arch-wide in-tree is safe.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/Kconfig
@@ -109,7 +109,14 @@
 	select HAVE_FUNCTION_GRAPH_TRACER
 	select HAVE_FUNCTION_TRACER if !XIP_KERNEL
 	select HAVE_GCC_PLUGINS
-	select HAVE_HW_BREAKPOINT if PERF_EVENTS && (CPU_V6 || CPU_V6K || CPU_V7)
+	# HAVE_HW_BREAKPOINT deliberately NOT selected on the steelhead build:
+	# the OMAP4460 is a fused HS part with secure debug locked, so
+	# enable_monitor_mode() can never set DSCR.MDBGEN (it logged
+	# "hw-breakpoint: Failed to enable monitor mode on CPU 0" every boot).
+	# perf/ptrace HW watchpoints cannot function on this silicon regardless;
+	# stock 3.0.8 did not build the feature either. Dropping the select
+	# matches stock and removes the boot warning with zero functional loss.
+	# (steelhead-only kernel; safe to drop arch-wide in this tree.)
 	select HAVE_IRQ_TIME_ACCOUNTING
 	select HAVE_KERNEL_GZIP
 	select HAVE_KERNEL_LZ4
